02/09/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivo Sanader is to visit Macedonia early next week, the government announced Wednesday (1 September). 
He will meet with counterpart Hari Kostov, President Branko Crvenkovski and other officials. 
The talks will focus on improving co-operation in all areas. 
The two countries also plan to sign an accord on their mutual quest for EU membership.
In other news, a top aide to Croatian President Stipe Mesic resigned on Tuesday after the EU said he was not welcome in any of its member states. 
In July, the Union added Zeljko Bagic's name to the list of people believed to be helping fugitive General Ante Gotovina evade justice. 
(AFP, HRT, HINA - 01/09/04)
